Also, ensure your getTermForWeek method is working correctly. Add this validation to it:

```javascript
getTermForWeek(week) {
    if (!this.courseData || !this.courseData.terms) return null;
    
    return this.courseData.terms.find(term => {
        if (!term || !term.startWeek || !term.weeks) return false;
        return week >= term.startWeek && week < term.startWeek + term.weeks;
    });
}
```

The main issue was that the renderTimeline() method wasn't properly handling cases where:

1. The DOM elements weren't ready
2. The total weeks or terms data was invalid
3. The container disappeared during rendering

These fixes add proper error handling, validation, and retry logic to ensure the timeline renders correctly.
